<text>Newton&apos;s Cradle

Run this model to figure out what moves down the line of balls. 
   
Try to understand why the red color moves from one atom to the next. 

  
  

It is easier to understand this if you remove one of the moving atoms so only one collides. 
   Use the reset button (the left-most button at the bottom of the model) and then the 
   eraser (the button with scissors) to cut out an atom. 
With some experimenting, you should be able to answer these important questions.

      

To answer the next question, use the eraser tool to eliminate all but one white atom.     
Run this two-atom model. 
      


This experiment shows what a shockwave looks like. 
Next explore a shockwave with lots of atoms. 
Go to next model--&gt;

Here is another simulation of Newton&apos;s Cradle:
http://www.school-for-champions.com/science/newtons_cradle.htm
</text>
